ct. Furthermore, as shown in the gif below, the joint itself moves as `Joint::SetPosition` is called with different angles\r\n\r\n![Peek 2018-12-07 17-09.gif](data/bitbucket.org/repo/jgXqbo/images/3318440981-Peek_2018-12-07_17-09.gif)\r\n\r\nHere is the same set of angles using ODE\r\n\r\n![Peek 2018-12-07 17-08.gif](data/bitbucket.org/repo/jgXqbo/images/1113494955-Peek_2018-12-07_17-08.gif)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>When using <code>Joint::SetPosition</code> using Bullet as the physics engine as shown in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2505/setaxis-implementation-incorrect-for-dart\" rel=\"nofollow\">this</a> regression test, if the joint position is set to a value not on the axis of the joint, the motion of the attached link is incorrect. Furthermore, as shown in the gif below, the joint itself moves as <code>Joint::SetPosition</code> is called with different angles</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Peek 2018-12-07 17-09.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/jgXqbo/images/3318440981-Peek_2018-12-07_17-09.gif\" /></p>\n<p>Here is the same set of angles using ODE</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Peek 2018-12-07 17-08.gif\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/jgXqbo/images/1113494955-Peek_2018-12-07_17-08.gif\" /></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "9.0", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/242746.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2018-12-08T00:45:55.287205+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2018-12-10T16:14:48.516624+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 2573}